title: River Walbrook (culvert)
description:
(I'll edit this tag again, adding more info, address, category, polygon, etc., on later)

The River Walbrook enters the Thames underneath Cannon Street Railway Station, but you'll have be in a boat on the Thames to see it.

Walbrook street to the north runs along the original line of the river.  The river was used by the Romans who built the Temple of Mithras (Victoria Street) across it.  A modern church, St Stephens, Walbrook is built just to the east of the course of this river.
